What will be the output of the following C program?

#include <stdio.h>
#define SQR(x) x*x
int main() {
    int a = 3;
    int b = SQR(a+2);
    printf("%d", b);
    return 0;
}

What will be the output of the following C code snippet?

int a = 10;
int *p = &a;
int **q = &p;
printf("%d", **q);

What will be the output of the following code?
int a = 5, b = 2;
printf("%d", a & b | a ^ b);
